The Caro-Kann Defense (c6):

This is a solid response to 1.e4.
The Caro-Kann starts with 1.e4 c6, planning to support the d5 pawn push on the next move.
It is known for providing black a solid, but dynamic position.
Major lines include the Classical Variation, the Advance Variation, and the Panov-Botvinnik Attack.